 "narr": {
  "Aqua Roma": "Aqua Roma W27: 262 bookings on ~4918 attributed users (pagePath aquanyc), CVR ~5.3%. Combined Aqua NYC is well ahead of LY (298 vs 190 bookings, +57%) on 6,305 users vs 3,685 LY. Meta rebounded to $21.8/schedule (74 sched) after the token outage; Google spend stepped up to $1,181 for 42 conversions ($28.1 CPA). Post-holiday demand recovered strongly.",
  "Aqua Kyoto": "Aqua Kyoto NYC (new 2026 venue) W27: 36 bookings on ~1387 users (pagePath aquakyotonyc), CVR ~2.6% \u2014 its best week yet on both volume and rate. No LY comparison \u2014 launched this year. Ad panels below are the shared Aqua New York account (Roma + Kyoto combined).",
  "Hutong NYC": "Hutong NYC W27: 105 bookings on 2,184 users, CVR 4.8%. Users are -60% YoY and bookings -71% \u2014 still the deepest decline in the portfolio, though traffic is up 15% WoW off the holiday trough. Meta improved sharply to $47.9/schedule (16 sched on $766 spend) after three broken weeks; Google holds at $46.8/conv. Paid media is stabilising but the traffic base needs a reset.",
  "Hutong Miami": "Hutong Miami W27: 61 bookings on 1,572 users, CVR 3.9%. Users -42% YoY as last week's Meta reach push unwound (spend down from $6,005 to $2,509). Bookings 61 vs 81 LY. Meta CPA improved to $114.1/schedule from $111 but is still 4x LY; Google steady at $61.2/conv. The July 4th spike was not sustained."
